15 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
16 SECTION 1. That the Heading for Chapter 24, Title 41, Idaho Code, be,
17 and the same is hereby amended to read as follows:
18 CHAPTER 24
19 PROPERTY INSURANCE CONTRACTS
20 SECTION 2. That Chapter 24, Title 41, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
21 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
22 ignated as Section 41-2402, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
23 41-2402. IDAHO WILDFIRE RISK MITIGATION FUND ACT -- LEGISLATIVE IN-
24 TENT -- SHORT TITLE. It is the intent of the legislature to assist homeowners
25 and property owners in protecting their homes and property against wildfire
26 risks and to reduce or mitigate wildfire risk to property owners, thereby re-
27 ducing costs of property insurance, reducing or mitigating community-level
28 wildfire risks, and assisting in attracting and retaining insurers in the
29 property marketplace, by establishing the provisions of sections 41-2402
30 through 41-2405, Idaho Code, which shall be known and may be cited as the
31 "Idaho Wildfire Risk Mitigation Fund Act."
32 SECTION 3. That Chapter 24, Title 41, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
33 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
34 ignated as Section 41-2403, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
35 41-2403. WILDFIRE RISK MITIGATION FUND. (1) There is hereby created in
36 the state treasury the wildfire risk mitigation fund. The fund shall con-
37 sist of moneys deposited pursuant to section 41-2405, Idaho Code. Inter-
38 est earned on the investment of idle moneys in the fund shall be returned to
39 the fund. The fund is hereby continuously appropriated to the extent neces-

2
1 sary to accomplish the provisions of sections 41-2402 through 41-2405, Idaho
2 Code.
3 (2) The fund is established to:
4 (a) Receive funding from various sources;
5 (b) Improve access to property insurance in target areas; and
6 (c) Distribute funding to mitigate wildfire risk, including but not
7 limited to grants, matching programs, and educational efforts.
8 (3) The fund shall, at all times, be free from taxation of any kind.
9 (4) The director of the department of insurance may appoint an advisory
10 committee to assist in operation of the fund.
11 SECTION 4. That Chapter 24, Title 41, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
12 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
13 ignated as Section 41-2404, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
14 41-2404. POWERS AND AUTHORITY. The director of the department of in-
15 surance shall have the authority to:
16 (1) Promulgate rules, subject to legislative approval, to accomplish
17 the provisions of sections 41-2402 through 41-2405, Idaho Code; and
18 (2) Establish policies and procedures as may be necessary or convenient
19 for the implementation of the provision of sections 41-2402 through 41-2405,
20 Idaho Code, and the operation of the wildfire risk mitigation fund, includ-
21 ing for:
22 (a) The handling and accounting of assets and moneys and for the annual
23 fiscal reporting of such assets and moneys;
24 (b) Selecting an administrator and setting forth the powers and duties
25 of the administrator;
26 (c) Providing grants to citizens or communities for wildfire risk mit-
27 igation. Such grant amounts shall be limited in order to assist the
28 largest number of citizens and may require matching funds; and
29 (d) Funding property protection and fire prevention and mitigation ed-
30 ucation and resources.
31 SECTION 5. That Chapter 24, Title 41, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
32 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
33 ignated as Section 41-2405, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
34 41-2405. FUNDING. The Idaho wildfire risk mitigation fund shall be
35 funded from the following sources:
36 (1) The ongoing appropriation of premium tax authorized pursuant to
37 section 41-406(1)(e), Idaho Code;
38 (2) Excess stamping fees as recommended by the surplus line association
39 of Idaho or a delegated organization and approved by the director of the de-
40 partment of insurance; and
41 (3) Grants or other contributions available for fire prevention or mit-
42 igation, including private sector contributions.
43 SECTION 6. That Section 41-406, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
44 amended to read as follows:

