1 41-406. DEPOSIT AND REPORT OF FEES, LICENSES AND TAXES. (1) The direc-
2 tor shall transmit all taxes, fines and penalties collected by him to the
3 state treasurer as provided under section 59-1014, Idaho Code. The director
4 shall file with the state controller a statement of each deposit thus made.
5 All such funds received shall be deposited into the department of insurance
6 suspense account. Such funds shall be distributed as follows:
7 (a) The director may deposit up to twenty percent (20%) of the funds
8 received in the insurance refund account which is hereby created for
9 the purpose of repaying overpayments of any taxes, fines, and penalties
10 or other erroneous receipts. There is hereby appropriated out of the
11 insurance refund account so much thereof as shall be necessary for the
12 payment of refunds. Any unencumbered balance remaining in the insur-
13 ance refund account on June 30 of each and every year in excess of forty
14 thousand dollars ($40,000) shall be transferred to the general fund and
15 the state controller is hereby authorized and directed on such dates to
16 make such transfers unless the board of examiners, which is hereby au-
17 thorized to do so, changes the date of transfer or sum to be transferred.
18 (b) That portion of the premium tax, payable to the public employee re-
19 tirement fund as provided in section 59-1394, Idaho Code, shall be dis-
20 tributed to that fund.
21 (c) That portion of the premium tax necessary to cover administrative
22 costs incurred by the department in placing insurance companies or any
23 other insurance entities into receivership or under administrative su-
24 pervision, and such costs cannot be satisfied from the assets of these
25 companies or entities, shall be distributed to the insurance insolvency
26 administrative fund which is hereby created. There is hereby appro-
27 priated out of the insurance insolvency administrative fund so much
28 thereof as shall be necessary, but not to exceed two hundred thousand
29 dollars ($200,000) in any one (1) fiscal year, for the payment of the
30 department's administrative expenses incurred in carrying out such re-
31 ceiverships or supervision. A balance of one hundred thousand dollars
32 ($100,000) shall be maintained in this fund on June 30 of each year.
33 (d) After all other the deductions authorized in this section
34 paragraphs (b) and (c) of this subsection have been made, if the pre-
35 mium tax remaining exceeds forty-five million dollars ($45,000,000),
36 one-fourth (1/4) of such excess is hereby appropriated and shall be paid
37 to the Idaho individual high risk reinsurance pool established in chap-
38 ter 55, title 41, Idaho Code.
39 (e) After the deductions authorized in paragraphs (b) through (d) of
40 this subsection have been made, if the premium tax remaining exceeds
41 one hundred thirteen million dollars ($113,000,000), one-fourth (1/4)
42 of such excess is hereby appropriated and shall be paid to the wildfire
43 risk mitigation fund established in chapter 24, title 41, Idaho Code.
44 (e) (f) The balance of the premium tax, fines and penalties shall be
45 distributed to the general fund of the state of Idaho.
46 (f) (g) All moneys received for fees, licenses and miscellaneous
47 charges collected shall be distributed to the insurance administrative
